  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Typical barbarians harbor a fury that dwells within. Their rage grants them superior strength, durability, and speed. Barbarians who follow the Path of the Storm Herald learn instead to transform their rage into a mantle of primal magic that swirls around them. When in a fury, a barbarian of this path taps into nature to create powerful, magical effects.</p>\n<p>Storm heralds are typically elite champions who train alongside druids, rangers, and others sworn to protect the natural realm. Other storm heralds hone their craft in elite lodges founded in regions wracked by storms, in the frozen reaches at the worldâ€™s end, or deep in the hottest deserts.</p>\n<h3>Path of the Storm Herald Features</h3>\n<p>3rd Level: @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-class-features.lYXGiJNdfJK6vrO9]{Storm Aura}</p>\n<p>6th Level: @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-class-features.TrQTqfuFjB9bw8gX]{Storm Soul}</p>\n<p>10th Level: @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-class-features.3CKj9jvPyZ1Usg1U]{Shielding Storm}</p>\n<p>14th Level: @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-class-features.Uii0vzrIc4O3Q1iw]{Raging Storm}</p>",
